dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.os.PartyRoleUsesProcessesDetails
dataStructure.description:
This class defines the semantics of the PartyRoleUsesProcesses association. Since different PartyRoles have different privileges for working on and running the OperatingSystem, an association class is needed to accurately model these details.This association defines the semantics of how a particular PartyRole uses this OperatingSystem instance.

This association class is optional
dataStructure.label: PartyRoleUsesProcessesDetails

child.name: maxNumberProcesses
child.description:
This attribute defines the maximum number of processes that can be allocated to a particular PartyRole.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: maxNumberProcesses

child.name: currentNumberProcesses
child.description:
This attribute defines the current number of processes that can are used by this particular PartyRole.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: currentNumberProcesses
